    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Step 4. Measure Condition indicators at project start\"\nformat: html\n---\n\nWhile the project does have historical start date, biodiversity monitoring was conducted two weeks after the start date, thus, we did not need to use proxy sites.\n\nThe following [Table 7](#table7) includes the condition at project start for each indicator, and each subsection provides an explanation on how these were calculated.\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Table 7. Condition at Project Start for each Indicator</summary>\n\n::: terra-table-title\nTable 7. Condition at Project Start for each Indicator\n:::\n\n::: {#table7}\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"datatables html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-922ba18ce321fd8bfbfb\" style=\"width:100%;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-922ba18ce321fd8bfbfb\">{\"x\":{\"filter\":\"none\",\"vertical\":false,\"data\":[[\"Composition (Cm1)\",\"Composition (Cm2)\",\"Composition (Cm3)\",\"Structure (S1)\",\"Structure (S2)\"],[\"Species richness of herpetofauna\",\"Species richness of birds\",\"Species richness of mammals\",\"Aboveground biomass (MG DM ha-1)\",\"Forest canopy cover (%)\"],[\"46.000\",\"215.000\",\"31.000\",\"34.540\",\"49.050\"]],\"container\":\"<table class=\\\"stripe hover compact\\\">\\n  <thead>\\n    <tr>\\n      <th>Condition Component<\\/th>\\n      <th>Indicator Description<\\/th>\\n      <th>Condition value measured at project start<\\/th>\\n    <\\/tr>\\n  <\\/thead>\\n<\\/table>\",\"options\":{\"paging\":false,\"searching\":false,\"info\":false,\"ordering\":false,\"scrollX\":true,\"autoWidth\":false,\"columnDefs\":[{\"className\":\"dt-center\",\"targets\":\"_all\"},{\"name\":\"Condition Component\",\"targets\":0},{\"name\":\"Indicator Description\",\"targets\":1},{\"name\":\"Condition value measured at project start\",\"targets\":2}],\"order\":[],\"orderClasses\":false}},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n</details>\n\n## Mammal Species Richness\n\nEach camera trap had a unique name and GPS coordinate to identify which camera captured which animal. Once the raw data was collected and reviewed, it was aligned with the Nature Framework requirements. The data collected at each camera trap could have been associated with a different functional group, so each location was taken and added to the shapefile of the functional group.\n\nThen, this file was cross referenced to the raw data collected in the field according to the camera trap ID and coordinates. If the camera trap was in an area not described as Tropical/Sub-tropical dry forests, the data was excluded, as seen in [Table 8](#table8).\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Table 8. Camera Trap Data – Calakmul</summary>\n\n::: {#table8}\n:::\n\n::: terra-table-title\nTable 8. Camera Trap Data – Calakmul\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"datatables html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-d50f2b59799c40bdba25\" style=\"width:100%;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-d50f2b59799c40bdba25\">{\"x\":{\"filter\":\"none\",\"vertical\":false,\"data\":[[null,\"Cancabchen\",\"PointZ (-89.63114166259765625 19.15689086914062855 178.30799865722659092)\",\"1.5. Forest – Subtropical/tropical dry\",\"Habia fuscicauda\",\"Homo sapiens\",null,null,null,null,null,null,null,\"Chanchen\",\"PointZ (-89.22185890999999458 19.06071023000000153 100)\",\"1.5. Forest – Subtropical/tropical dry\",\"Odocoileus pandora\",null,null,null,\"Chunek\",\"PointZ (-89.16773766000000023 19.18777751000000009 98.00000000000001421)\",\"1.5. Forest – Subtropical/tropical dry\",\"Capra hircus\",\"Tapirus bairdii\",null,null,null,null,null,\"Cristobal Colón\",\"Herpailurus yaguaroundi\",\"Ortalis vetula\",\"Urocyon cinereoargenteus\",null,null,null,null,\"Felipe Angeles\",\"PointZ (-89.25234245000000044 18.20243925000000118 202)\",\"1.5. Forest – Subtropical/tr