  11<\\/th>\\n      <th>   12<\\/th>\\n      <th>   13<\\/th>\\n    <\\/tr>\\n  <\\/thead>\\n<\\/table>\",\"options\":{\"paging\":false,\"pageLength\":15,\"scrollX\":true,\"autoWidth\":false,\"columnDefs\":[{\"className\":\"dt-center\",\"targets\":\"_all\"},{\"name\":\"ID proyecto\",\"targets\":0},{\"name\":\"Punto Observ  ID\",\"targets\":1},{\"name\":\"Elevación\",\"targets\":2},{\"name\":\"Nombre observador\",\"targets\":3},{\"name\":\"   5\",\"targets\":4},{\"name\":\"   6\",\"targets\":5},{\"name\":\"   7\",\"targets\":6},{\"name\":\"   8\",\"targets\":7},{\"name\":\"   9\",\"targets\":8},{\"name\":\"   10\",\"targets\":9},{\"name\":\"   11\",\"targets\":10},{\"name\":\"   12\",\"targets\":11},{\"name\":\"   13\",\"targets\":12}],\"order\":[],\"orderClasses\":false,\"lengthMenu\":[10,15,25,50,100]}},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n</details>\n\nTo calculate the species richness, we measured the total number of species observed in each ejido and added them together for the Project Extent, while excluding any species that was found outside of the tropical/sub-tropical dry forests, as seen in [Table 11](#table11).\n\n### Aboveground Biomass\n\nTo ensure high-precision and replicable values of Aboveground Biomass (AGB), raw GEDI data was used: **Spaceborne LiDAR: NASA GEDI Level 4A (GEDI04_A_002)**\n\nThe Global Ecosystem Dynamics Investigation (GEDI) L4A Monthly dataset was utilized as the primary source for biomass calibration. GEDI provides high-resolution laser ranging observations of the Earth’s 3D structure from the International Space Station. Footprint-level estimates of Aboveground Biomass Density (AGBD) were extracted and used directly.\n\nGEDI’s LiDAR technology provides direct measurements of canopy height and vertical profile, which are more strongly correlated with biomass than passive optical signals alone. This minimizes the risk of \"signal saturation\" in high-biomass areas.\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>GEDI_AGB_2023_raw.tif</summary>\n\n[Download GEDI Aboveground Biomass Raster (2023)](files/GEDI_AGB_2023_raw.tif){.terra-button target=\"_blank\"}\n\n</details>\n\n### Canopy Cover\n\nThe canopy cover raster was retrieved from the NASA hub and the product is described in [Step H3](Step%208.html#step-h3-raster). Canopy Cover directly measures habitat structure and is highly sensitive to both ecosystem degradation and conversion.\n\nThe indicator has 10 years of continuous historical data, enabling regression-based forecasting as required by SD VISta for using historical conversion rates MODIS is a credible, globally recognized source with documented accuracy and validation Spatial resolution (250m) complies with SD VISta requirement of ≤300m.\n\nThe indicator is already used for program monitoring, ensuring consistency between baseline and verification. Compliance with Section 7.5.4: Dataset meets all data requirements including spatial resolution, temporal coverage, credible source, and sensitivity to habitat conversion.\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>MOD44B_TreeCover_2014-2023.tif</summary>\n\n[Download MOD44B Tree Cover Raster (2014–2023)](files/MOD44B_TreeCover_2014-2023.tif){.terra-button target=\"_blank\"}\n\n</details>\n",
